#   PUT tickets: reflog edits (stage / branch / tag)

`be put` is the reflog-write verb — stage files (into the `.be/wtlog` ULOG), set a branch tip, fast-forward a remote. No open tickets — landed ones kept as breadcrumbs below. The fix-and-land method is [Issues].

 -  [PUT-001] — **LANDED `d628fd67`.** `be put <sub>/<path>` now relays into a mounted submodule's own staging: `BEActSubsPut` (`beagle/BE.cli.c:2914`) routes each path-form arg that lands in a mount through `BERelaySub` to the sub's `be put`, parent-bound paths fall through to `sniff put`; honors `--nosub`, staging stays wtlog-only. Regression `test/put/12-sub-path-scoped` (passes WITH_SSH). Related: [[DIS-034]] (`be put <dir>` trailing-slash) is a separate PUT path-classification gap.

